name: Animal bite-Pre exposure prophylaxis
description: Three 2.5 IU/mL doses of rabies vaccine are given IM, one injection per day, on days 0, 7, and 21 or 28, in the deltoid area of adults or in the anterolateral thigh of young children.

name: Animal bite-Post exposure treatment
description: One dose of the vaccine should be administered on days 0, 3, 7, 14 and 28. Given in the deltoid region or, for young children, into the antero-lateral area of the thigh muscle
